@jmg100001 Hi, if you have submitted a case for compensation to our Customer Care department, they have a processing time of 6-8 weeks

@o07557174 Hi, for information about delayed baggage, you need to contact the baggage service at the airport that was your final destination. The phone number for SAS Baggage Service in Oslo is +47 64812700
//Henrik

@ErtseyE Hi, try different browsers, but if you still can't make a report online, you need to call the baggage service at the airport that was your final destination. You can find the phone number at this link https://t.co/We1FdD7ZiM

@Tinatalks22 Hi, if your flight has been changed and your new option doesn't fit, you can call us or contact us via chat to rebook free of charge
//Henrik

@MCampoyCruz Hi, there are limited youth tickets available which means they sell out faster than regular tickets. This is why you often see more regular ticket available than youth.
//Henrik

//Henrik

@CLaurenWhicker Hi there!
I recommend you to report your bag missing here: https://t.co/ojhL9dIf2x and the tracing will then immediately start.
You can follow the process through: https://t.co/2zwsPbhQFU

You can also reach BaggageService here: https://t.co/We1FdD7ZiM
Best regards, Angelica

@Weaverwerx Hi! 

If you had a refundable voucher then you can go to https://t.co/YQFS6XMvcp and write in your voucher code and then click on request a refund. But if you don't get that as an alternative then it's sadly not possible. We can't extend our vouchers.

Kind regards, 
Dennis

Kind regards,
Dennis

@CollabKey Hi! 

Okay, the best i can recommend is to contact our customer service via chat or by phone, as we don't have an email you can use. We do have a long queue right now, but we are working on it as fast as possible.

Kind regards,
Dennis

@632f25e8946645a Hi! 

No they won't stop searching for it, but if 21 days has passed then it's sadly unlikely that they will find it. So i recommend that you send in a claim to us via the form we sent earlier, so we can help you have a look at a compensation.

Kind regards,
Dennis
